===Etymology===
From {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|fr|blond}} {{g|m}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|blond|blond, blont}}, from {{etyl|frk|en}} {{m|frk|*blund||a mixed color between golden and light-brown}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*blundaz||mixed, blinding}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*bʰlendʰ-||to become turbid, see badly, go blind}}. Compare {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|blondenfeax|''blonden''feax|grey-haired}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|blandan||to mix}}. More at {{l|en|blend}}.

Alternative etymology connects {{etyl|frk|-}} {{m|frk|*blund}} to {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*blundaz||blond}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*bʰl̥ndʰ-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*bʰlendʰ-||blond, red-haired}}. If so, then it would be cognate with {{etyl|sa|-}} {{m|sa|ब्रध्न||tr=bradhná|ruddy, pale red, yellowish}}.

